    "Elements of the",
    "National Communism or 'NazComm' is a communism practiced at a national level. National communism recognises that both globalist capitalism",
    "and international communism aim to destroy traditional proletariat culture. We find our basis in the writings of Marx, Engels, Lenin, Stalin, Kim",
    "Il-Sung, etc. We recognise that a communist revolution will inevitably begin at a national level as a struggle between proletariat and bourgeoisie",
    "made inevitable by the modern conditions of capitalism. National communism recognises that the international bourgeoisie will attempt to destroy",
    "all attempts at escape from capitalism, therefore, we stress the need for self-sustaining national communes, capable of resisting globalist capital-",
    "ist interference. Furthermore, we promote barracks communism to resist any attempted imperialist invasion."
